title: The Kalam and Endless Future: 5 Arguments with Joe Schmid
description:
The second premise of the kalam argument is typically defended by a quite general argument against the possibility of actual infinities. One of the issues with the argument, however, is that it assumes the past is numerable, while the future is not. In this video, I'm joined by Joe Schmid from @MajestyofReason to offer five arguments against this assumption.
